28/11/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The Central Elections Commission (CEC) announced on Monday (November 28th) that it has drafted a proposal aimed at resolving an ongoing dispute over the election of a seventh member of local election commissions. 
The issue is one of several that have blocked electoral reform and preparations for winter municipal elections. 
By law, the governing majority names three members, and the opposition the other three. 
According to the CEC proposal, a lot would be drawn, to determine which party appoints the seventh member in the respective constituencies. 
(Albanian News - 28/11/06)
